
[1]anthracite

   AN'THRACITE, n. [Gr. a burning coal; infra.]

   Slaty glance-coal, or columnar glance coal; that species of coal which
   has a shining luster, approaching to metallic, and which burns without
   smoke, and with intense heat. It consists essentially of carbon.
